[normal] In October 2013 we won the public sector 
[normal]category award in PWC’s
[normal] 
[normal]Building Public Trust Awards for our progress towards integrated reporting.
[normal] This is separate from and in addition to the Coastal Communities Fund (CCF). The CCF was set up by HM Treasury and is administered by the Big Lottery Fund. It consists of 50 per cent of the annual gross revenues from The Crown Estate’s marine activities. 
[normal]From 2012/13 to 2015/16, this will total £10.85 million. CCF is aimed at projects that promote sustainable economic development.
